<hl>
<seg id=1> Ding Hao, a deformity, growing up in Chinese Orphanage, became the first University student. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Hangzhou, 1 September, by Zhu Guoxian, Guan Zhehui Ding Hao, who had lived in Hangzhou Children's Orphanage since his childhood, received the Letter of Acceptance from Hangzhou University, and became a student of the Department of Philosophy and Social Sciences. </seg>
<seg id=3> It's known that 19 year-old Ding Hao was the first university student who was raised by an orphanage after the liberation. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Ding Hao said: " After receiving the Letter of Acceptance, I really wanted to jump with joy". However he could not express himself by "jumping". </seg>
<seg id=5> At 3, he contracted infantile paralysis because of a high fever, and an orphanage adopted him that year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He completed his primary schooling in the orphanage, and went to a village secondary school nearby. </seg>
<seg id=7> At the beginning, the teachers of the orphanage helped him travel to and from the school. He lived in the school after the second year. No matter how bad the weather was, he never missed his classes, and he came back to his orphanage on Saturdays. </seg>
<seg id=8> This year, he took part in the entrance examinations to the university, and he was qualified to be a student of Hongzhou University. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Ding Hao's success was an embodiment of the care from all walks of life. </seg>
<seg id=10> The Children's Orphanage had always protected and cared about him for 16 years. Last year, they spent about 3,000 Yuan only on his tuition, teaching materials, and nutritious food. </seg>
<seg id=11> He was offered help from all walks of life. </seg>
<seg id=12> Knowing that Ding Hao went to the university, Hongzhou Longchang Grain and Oil Trade Company donated 20,000 Yuan for his study, and the factory of artificial limb gave him wheelchair, walking stick, etc. </seg>
</p>
